caption: Awesome and flavorful food, I like the character this place has, and the cashiers were helpful. Will definitely come back.

Ordered 3 things. Rolls were decent but they forgot to give sauce and Wasabi. The rib bento bowl however was horrible. Veges were way too salty, the 7 grain rice was like porridge, wet and soggy and the ribs were meh.
Best sushi in the neighborhood. Consistently great.
I regularly arrive grabbing some food here. I love the prompt customer service and well cooked food. They never disappoint.
Fantastic and delightful food, I liked the mood this place has, and the employees were very welcoming. Will definitely visit here again.
The place offers a large variety of delicious food. I liked dining here. The employees are always very friendly, prices are reasonable and the place is always neat.

Food overall good quality and pretty tasty.  I did expect bigger portions for the prices. The Yaki Udon, it came in small container compared to other Japanese restaurants I have ordered from, but not bad. The chicken teriyaki bento box was were I was soo disappointed. Mostly vegetables and tempura veggies I didnt want. My kids didnt even like it, usually that's their favorite chicken teriyaki. It had a small amount of chicken, barely a full breast of chicken. And a tiny serving of rice was on the side, (Imagine a icee cup). Definitely disappointed in the portions for those 2 meals, since they were a main dinner and most expensive. Other stores definitely serve more especially chicken teriyaki dinner. But the Taste was good (aside from overly added sesame seasoning on top of everything. Should be an option to not add it) Chicken tempura/Shrimp tempura/cali rolls all excellent and best thing out of my order!! Great so good.  Delivery took a bit long although I understand quarantine and protest have delayed alot. So I give them the benefit of the doubt, and once I called about the wait my food arrived 15 minutes later. So Great customer service. Will be giving them a try again. Just hope they work on portion size for the prices.
I am very satisfied with this dinner. The chicken is very tender, the sauce is very delicious, and the portion is very large. I will recommend it to friends to try it.
(Translated by Google) Very good service, very fresh ingredients  (Original) 服务态度很好   很新鲜的食材
They have fresh fish ,and best kitchen food,amazing!
Great sushi at a great price..
Expensive for the quality of sushi. Would definitely select another Japanese restaurant in this price range.

Amazing food and service. Came here for Christmas day dinner and while we were the only ones there the staff were super nice and on top of things. Sushi and sashimi were fresh and delicious. Crispy duck app while not what I expected was absolutely delicious. Miso soup was some of the best I've had and the avacado salad and edamame were also fresh and tasty. With drinks and tip the bill came to $100 for 2 and was way more than enough food. Will definitely be back.

This is a really good place to have sushi. I always come here to get sushi with my best friend after college. The service is excellent! I will always come back here! It is a lot better than the sushi place which is right across. We were served by Dylan, he is great!
Overall the food was good but even thou it’s a lunch special please pay attention to what you are putting in it. One bad cherry tomato (only one) jeopardize higher rating.
best lunch special deal in the area.  highly recommend for lunch.  very friendly staff and little to no wait.

Didn't like the staff, We didnt understand what she was telling us and they have us check without even asking, very rude. Also we didnt give the check to the side so she couldn't take it because we wanted to talk and sit for longer but she was constantly walking around waiting for it, so obviously. Food was fine
Great spot! Good food, reasonable prices! Dirty Grey Goose martini is 12$ and it comes almost in a bucket! lol Definitely will be back!

I’ll give this place a 8/10. It’s actually been almost a month since I’ve been here, and I just forgot to review this place. The sushi is excellent. I remember the taste was good. The only thing was that I remember we waited forever for the sushi to come out. We were not very patient, but that wait time failed to meet our expectations.

Friendly staff and good quality food. Have gone there several times with colleagues for just a casual lunch, to celebrate birthday or for large group farewell, and always had great customer service experience. Once we even ordered in advance when we were a group of 20, and all orders came in super quick and completely accurate. Good selection of vegetarian sushi too!
The food is regularly well prepared and delicious, workers provides fantastic customer service. I like how neat it is and atmosphere. Keep up the good work.
Don't go if your Black. Had to seat self. No service at all while they waited on others
Fantastic spot to eat food when in a hurry. The customer service is prompt, rates are affordable, excellent character. Keep up the good work
My favorite japanesse restaurant in Brooklyn

Was excited to try here. Was very disappointed with my order and the attitude I recieved after saying the fruit in my dish made my stomach slightly upset. Was willing to order a different meal and still wanted to try the sushi. After the attitude I recieved I decided to just pay my bill, leave and not ordering anything else. I gave two star because the Kani salad was delicious.
Nice place relax to enjoy Japanese food.
(Translated by Google) Pleasant surprise good food good attention  (Original) Grata sorpresa  buena comida buena atencion
Great food and service!
It was amazing specially 2 for 1 drinks.. everything tested fresh. The young lady waiting on us was a lil bit off. But the food made up 4 that.
Terrible service
Price was fair. Venue ok. Food could have been better
Fairly inexpensive and good
My favorite restaurant!
Believe me when I say the Shirley Temples are amazing
Always good
Great sushi and sashimi
Two for one drinks and a great satoshi bowl, what could be bad.

Yet another pleasant surprise in Brooklyn Heights. I got sushi rolls (which were great and had a generous amount of fish). My coworker got the $10 lunch box special. Along with the main dish the lunch box special was served with soup, salad, a California roll, edamame, rice, vegetables... all delicious (I eat her leftovers). Cheap beer, too. Can’t beat the lunch special.
Great food and service as well

Great menu with high quality sushi, and wide variety at that. The cooked food is just as incredible, especially the Hibachi Filet Mignon with Fried Rice; worth the extra few dollars versus the Hibachi Steak. Service was good and the price point is fair for the quality of the food.
If you really need Japanese food and in the area, this will do but it’s not great nor something to really go back for.
Really good Japanese food in enormous portions with a reasonable price.
Great food and service
Terrible service.. Not even a simply thank you.
Lunch is good, dinner is good
Great service. Great food.
Good options for sushi. Nice and quick service. The only bad thing was the restroom. They need better lighting and clean it more often. Overall it's a good place for sushi.
Excellent food, great prices.

Mostly great sushi, although the eel was disappointing. Drinks are reasonably priced. If you're not going for sake or beer and are visiting before 11pm, then drinks will be not only reasonable but cheap. Atmosphere is nice and friendly.
Very good sushi at a good price, good service

Pretty nice place. I tried their Kalbi appetizer and Nabeyahi Udon Soup and Pork Katsu with fried rice entree. I am not a big fan of their Udon broth but enjoyed their service and everything else. Friendly staff and wonderful service.
Pretty average sushi. We’ve had better sushi elsewhere in the city, but service was good and there were plenty of options. Prices seemed fair too.
Love coming here!

Excellent White Russians and black Russians. The Asian waiters are so lovely and caring and competent. I've never had one bite of food there. But I would definitely go back. They never play obnoxious music in  a loud manner!!!
The place looks chic! The food was great, especially the peanut avocado roll. The service was decent not that bad. Overall it was great!
Great food, awesome location and attentive service. The location is large enough that lunches are never packed, also there are great lunch deals. Great quality of food and excellent value for money

We came here on the 4th of July with my 1 yr old son, teenage daughter and my husband. It was at night right after the fireworks but it wasn't busy at all. They only had 2 or 3 servers on and there was only 5 tables of occupancy. Once we were sat no one came over to us for over 20 mins. I had to get up to ask for service at this point. Once someone finally came over they took our order but I had to constantly ask to have our water filled up. They then put our order in wrong and looked at us like they expected us to eat the wrong ordered food. They finally gave us our food but with no utensils. The food was good but the service was horrible. Definitely won't see me again.

Very good Japanese food if you happen to be in the Brooklyn heights area. Its also near a favorite ramen spot of mine called Kagone. Ozu is usually not too crowded, and even when it is, its still tolerable. The prices arent too high. Bring friends!
Very bad sushi roll. They are so dirty, trust me! Do not eat Chinese Sushi!
Very good food but a tiny bit pricey. Will be worth it to some.
Great Japanese-American restaurant with excellent service!  Highly recommend.

Seems like they focus so much on take-out the people who are dining in get shafted. Sushi is OK, for a Chinese-operated sushi spot, no better or worse. Hibachi is decent. However, service is atrocious. 30 minutes to get water on the table, another 30 minutes to get drinks. We had an emergency with our child and we asked for our food to go after it came to the table  (don't ask how long that took), and were ignored 3 times. My wife went to the waiters station to pack our own food to go after 10 minutes of waiting. I guess they mean well but staff has zero training, and management has zero concerns for what's going on in restaurant.
Some of the best sushi, and their cocktails are amazing. Great for a dinner with friends or a date.
Great food.  Be sure to ask about the soup of the day.
Great place
Best ever
Yummy Sushi
Nice ambience sushi is good the fish and the rice rightly made. One of the best sushi I taste around the area. Try the chef special. 👌
Excellent place. Great food and atmosphere

Walked across the Brooklyn Bridge and got lost. Stumbled upon this place looking for the Subway back to Manhattan and was surprised. We enjoyed a nice meal with good service for a fair price. Made getting lost worthwhile.
Outstanding sushi, wide variety of saki, great atmosphere. Owner was friendly and great to talk to!
Do not order take out. Expect 90 minutes wait.
Great place for Breakfast
Had an inedible yellowtail hand roll. A majority if the hand roll “specials” had spicy sauces. They have some creative dishes. Enjoyed the saki martinis. We will not go back!
The food is very delicious

Walked in 3 min prior to end of lunch special and was attended professionally. Ordered the best Hibachi chicken, amazing soup w/ bits of tofu and salad. Definitely one of the best lunch specials, near CUNY City Tech.
Love it here! My son can't get enough!
Food and drink are quite good. Delivery is efficient.

(Translated by Google) Quality food, wide and diversified menu, drinks list also with a good range of products.  (Original) Comida de qualidade, cardápio amplo e diversificado, carta de bebidas também com uma boa gama de produtos.

Horrible! Very slow service! Their sushi pieces were the tiniest pieces l've ever seen! I went there to enjoy my lunch with my wife and all we experienced was anxiety! They forgot one of our orders! It has never happened to me even in the busiest restaurants! It was a shame!! I don't know how they survive with this poor service in Brooklyn!

I would give them zero if I could! I personally believe you should not go to any random place to have sushi but today we really wanted to eat sushi for lunch and we end up here! First of, the waitress seemed very confused and not focused on her job! So I repeated my order twice loudly! The restaurant was really empty but it took them 40 min to prepare our food! AND she was simply forgotten to place my order!!!! So it took more time for me ( my husband was already eating his lunch ) Now it's time to talk about the food itself! We ordered lunch specials and the sushi pieces were really small as it was cheaper! My rolls were not looking good and they would tear apart while I was picking them up! I won't go there anymore and I don't suggest it to anyone! They need some real changes!
Good food!
Came here for lunch. They have a lot of great options for lunch specials. Food and service we're pretty good. The atmosphere is a bit dark and depressing, though

We have been ordering from them over the years, and every other day. My coworkers and I usually order for over $150 each time. Lately their fish has been rubbery and has smell, also their portions of sashimi got smaller. I called and addressed the issue first, and mentioned that if this will continue happening we will stop ordering. The girl on the phone said that everyone has different taste.
Great drinks. The oysters are unbelievable- a must gavw. The Pad Thai is excellent. Highly recommended!!!
Love this place, best spot for sushi in Brooklyn Heighs area in my opinion. Always get the rock and roll sushi roll.
The lunch special of shrimp tempura is great with a soup and salad
Great Japanese cusine place. Food served beautifully and taste good.
Food is bad, just straight up bad. Service is ok.
They used to have pretty lights under the sushi ice, but then now they don't. I think.

Great local spot. Creative dishes. Fish is fresh. The food is plated beautifully. Waitresses are friendly and they are great on the service aspect (ie. Refilling waters, tea, swapping plates etc). I come frequently. Yankee sandwich is a must as well as their Kalbi appetizer.
Good sushi, decent price. 2 for 1 drinks until 11.
Sushi good any day of the week. Awesome customer service
Great food with awesome lunch specials
Great sushi and sashimi, good service
Found this place walking by and was impressed. Good food + drink specials.
Always good sushi, buy 1 get 1 drinks.
THIS PLACE IS BOSS. Sushi is amazing. Staff is nice.

(Translated by Google) The best sushi in NY, if you like Japanese cuisine, must visit at a very good price, recommended 100%  (Original) El mejor sushi de NY, si te gusta la gastronomia japonesa, obligada visita a un precio muy bueno, recomendable 100%
The friendly staff and dedicated staff is best feature of Ozu. The food is alright, probably not the best sushi you'll ever have. Drinks are strong, sometimes too strong.
Two for one drink......  You can go wrong.

NEW OWNERS ARE GREAT!  This is one of best sushi places in Brooklyn Heights. I live in Los Angeles and stumbled on this place during a business trip 8 months ago. I come to NY on business 4-5 times per year. Although I stay in Manhattan, I always make a couple of trips to Ozu to visit the owner Lee, his wife Maggie, and the entire staff.  Lee and Maggie bought Ozu from the previous owners about a year ago so whatever review you read prior to then may not apply.  Everyone at Ozu is wonderful. Lee and Maggie have turned Ozu into a most enjoyable experience. The sushi is always fresh and reasonably priced. The service is friendly and unobtrusive.  I always sit at the sushi bar and have great conversations with Lee and several local regulars who  have nothing but praise for this place.  I highly recommend Ozu!
This place is never too crowded but the food and drinks are great! They have a BOGO deal on almost all their drinks.
Great food. Very expensive
Amazing, fresh sushi and very interesting combinations. Also very generous with drinks. Definitely coming back!
Some of the freshest raw fish I've ever tasted... Incredible crispy duck roll too!

This is my favorite Japanese join. The food is fresh and not over price. I also like the presentation eps. The dry ice with led lights that come with some dishes. The interior design is minimalistic and contempary. It is also very well kept and clean.  Highly recommend the rainbow ball roll and crispy duck roll.  Go during the week days and they offer 1 for 1 drinks. Highly recommend this eatery.

Not a genuine Japanese restaurant. The food didn't have an authentic Japanese taste. I ordered soba noodles and the noodles weren't soba but rather ramen. The soup tasted completely wrong and had random ingredients in it.
I like to order the bento box or kitchen box because rice and soup is included. I like the crunchy tuna roll. The food is very good and service is very friendly. The prices are reasonable.

Sadly I can only attest to the delivery services of this place but it's really good! I had a big lunch order which they aced and all the food was fresh and well-prepared. This is definitely going in the regular rotation.
Solid fallback for when Iron Chef has a long line.
